SIMPLE: although
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Although
<hw>Al*though"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>conj.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>All</ets> + <ets>though</ets>; OE. <ets>al
thagh</ets>.]</ety> <def>Grant all this; be it that; supposing that;
notwithstanding; though.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Although</qex> all shall be offended, yet will not I.</q>
<rj><qau>Mark xiv. 29.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- <er>Although</er>, <er>Though</er>.</syn> <usage>
<xex>Although</xex>, which originally was perhaps more emphatic than
<xex>though</xex>, is now interchangeable with it in the sense given
above. Euphonic consideration determines the choice.</usage>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Altiloquence</ent>⟦br⟧
